Mado Paris – Authentic French Bakery & Cafe in Rock Hill, SC (Charlotte, NC Area)

At Mado, everything is homemade from scratch. We bring the true taste of France to the Carolinas with authentic French pastries, artisan breads, and specialty drinks.

🍰 Desserts & Pastries: Tarts, choux, and entremets, perfect for a sweet treat or celebration.
🥐 Viennoiseries: Buttery croissants (classic, chocolate, almond, apple… and more).
🍞 Artisan Breads: Sourdough baguettes, brioche, and savory bread, made with traditional French flour.
☕ Drinks: espresso, flavored lattes, cold-pressed French juices.

🏙️ Perfect for a coffee date, business meeting, or fresh-baked bread to take home.

📍 Rock Hill, SC | Serving the Charlotte, NC area

I really hope Serge figures out a way to have food there for us in the late afternoon. It was super disappointing to see pastries that would only be available for the next day. Maybe you can make some basic snacks available? Packaged cookies that can survive a shelf life of a couple days? Basic croissants that will always be available for anyone who comes in at the end of the day before you close?  I'm not a coffee person, I'm not going to be coming in the mornings, and I don't enjoy drinking without something small to eat if I plan on hanging out over there for a while. Also, there were not many hot tea options for me.  I'd really appreciate seeing more food and drink options in the afternoons. And also, smaller, less fancy and more affordable desert and snack options in the late afternoon. If you find a way to offer me that, I'll consider coming to visit on a regular basis.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Natalie,

Thank you for your feedback. We’re glad you enjoy the quality and authenticity of our pastries: that’s what we’re most proud of.

That said, we did want to address your comments about the afternoon availability. We understand your frustration, but it’s important to clarify: our pastries are made fresh from scratch every morning, using traditional techniques and premium ingredients. That means we don’t mass-produce, freeze, or keep items with long shelf lives and that’s a deliberate choice. It’s the essence of our bakery, and we stand by it.

Of course we’d love to have pastries available at all hours but running a real bakery with real constraints (human, financial, and operational) is way more complex than it seems. 

So for now, if you want the best selection, you come early. That’s how it works at Mado!

We don’t believe in compromising the integrity of our products just to have “something left” at the end of the day. If your priority is guaranteed availability in the afternoon, there are plenty of other places in town that can satisfy your afternoon cravings when we’re out of pastries.

Still, thank you for visiting and we hope you’ll understand that what makes our place unique is also what limits its availability.

reviews_data.review_text:
Overpriced and dry croissants… when a complaint was made, it was completely disregarded and brushed off.

*Thank you for the same response that you gave me via another avenue. My order was $50+ bc I ordered more than croissants. The total was NOT given to me before the food items, so I didn’t feel like I could refuse them.
Hope this helps.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hello,

You initially reached out to us with your concerns, and we took the time to respond to you directly.

We always welcome feedback, as it helps us improve and grow. However, your message contained inconsistencies that we felt necessary to clarify. Your decision to post this comment here further confirms our initial assumption—it appears to be driven more by frustration than by a genuine concern, simply because our response may not have been what you expected.

That being said, whether public or by direct message on Facebook, our response remains the same:

Thank you for your feedback. We always appreciate hearing from our customers, as it allows us to maintain our high-quality standards.

Regarding pricing, our croissants are priced at $5.50, with the most expensive one at $6.00. Even at the highest price point, purchasing five croissants would total $30.00 before tax. With our 7% sales tax, the final amount would be $32.10, which does not match the “$50+” you mentioned. Additionally, at our drive-thru, the total amount is always announced before proceeding with the transaction, ensuring that each customer is fully aware of the price before handing over their card.

Furthermore, you mentioned that you have always loved and recommended our bakery, which implies that you have ordered from us before. Our prices (for the croissants) have remained unchanged since January 2024, despite the increase in the cost of raw materials that we import directly from France, as well as rising transportation expenses. If you have not visited us in a while, please note that our croissants have only increased by $1 since we opened in 2020, which is a very moderate adjustment considering the economic context.

Regarding the quality of our croissants, we are a small artisan bakery, not a large chain. We produce a limited quantity each day—a maximum of 10 trays of croissants—and every batch is carefully proofed, baked, and inspected by our chef before being served. We have never received feedback indicating that our croissants were dry. In fact, our recent reviews often highlight the richness of our croissants. Given our rigorous process and consistent quality, this feedback is surprising to us.

That being said, we understand that taste is subjective. If the croissants were not to your liking, we would have appreciated hearing from you directly. While we cannot accept returned food items due to health regulations, we always encourage open communication with our customers.

We take pride in using premium-quality ingredients, authentic French baking techniques and high quality service. We remain committed to providing the best experience possible, as reflected in our 4.9/5 rating with over 600 reviews on Google Business. None of which mention dryness as a concern.

Have a great week
Best regards

Hello Hope,

At Mado, we stay true to the authentic French tradition by using only high-quality ingredients, including AOP Isigny butter, imported directly from France which might be different from what you’re used to.

As for the slight sweetness you mentioned, we apply a very ligh homemade syrup coating to our croissants to enhance their golden finish, but it’s very subtle and shouldn’t make the croissant overly sweet. So this is not coming from the ustensils.

We understand your frustration, but it’s important to clarify: our pastries are made fresh from scratch every morning, using traditional techniques and premium ingredients. That means we don’t mass-produce, freeze, or keep items with long shelf lives and that’s a deliberate choice. It’s the essence of our bakery, and we stand by it.

Of course we’d love to have pastries available at all hours but running a real bakery with real constraints (human, financial, and operational) is way more complex than it seems. 

So for now, if you want the best selection, you come early. That’s how it works at Mado!

We don’t believe in compromising the integrity of our products just to have “something left” at the end of the day. If your priority is guaranteed availability in the afternoon, there are plenty of other places in town that can satisfy your afternoon cravings when we’re out of pastries.

Still, thank you for visiting and we hope you’ll understand that what makes our place unique is also what limits its availability.

Hello,

You initially reached out to us with your concerns, and we took the time to respond to you directly.

We always welcome feedback, as it helps us improve and grow. However, your message contained inconsistencies that we felt necessary to clarify. Your decision to post this comment here further confirms our initial assumption—it appears to be driven more by frustration than by a genuine concern, simply because our response may not have been what you expected.

That being said, whether public or by direct message on Facebook, our response remains the same:

Thank you for your feedback. We always appreciate hearing from our customers, as it allows us to maintain our high-quality standards.

Regarding pricing, our croissants are priced at $5.50, with the most expensive one at $6.00. Even at the highest price point, purchasing five croissants would total $30.00 before tax. With our 7% sales tax, the final amount would be $32.10, which does not match the “$50+” you mentioned. Additionally, at our drive-thru, the total amount is always announced before proceeding with the transaction, ensuring that each customer is fully aware of the price before handing over their card.

Furthermore, you mentioned that you have always loved and recommended our bakery, which implies that you have ordered from us before. Our prices (for the croissants) have remained unchanged since January 2024, despite the increase in the cost of raw materials that we import directly from France, as well as rising transportation expenses. If you have not visited us in a while, please note that our croissants have only increased by $1 since we opened in 2020, which is a very moderate adjustment considering the economic context.

Regarding the quality of our croissants, we are a small artisan bakery, not a large chain. We produce a limited quantity each day—a maximum of 10 trays of croissants—and every batch is carefully proofed, baked, and inspected by our chef before being served. We have never received feedback indicating that our croissants were dry. In fact, our recent reviews often highlight the richness of our croissants. Given our rigorous process and consistent quality, this feedback is surprising to us.

That being said, we understand that taste is subjective. If the croissants were not to your liking, we would have appreciated hearing from you directly. While we cannot accept returned food items due to health regulations, we always encourage open communication with our customers.

We take pride in using premium-quality ingredients, authentic French baking techniques and high quality service. We remain committed to providing the best experience possible, as reflected in our 4.9/5 rating with over 600 reviews on Google Business. None of which mention dryness as a concern.

Have a great week
Best regards
